    "body": "### Problem\n\nTyping `g CTRL-G` in visual mode does not show the information about the selected region. Normal mode is working.\n\nThis is a regression bug. The first commit with this issue is 9bbbeb60e355844780db0aef955e860d68ac0342.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* `nvim --clean`\n* Insert some text\n* Enter visual mode\n* Type `g CTRL-g`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDisplays word, character, line, and byte counts for the visually selected region\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nnightly 0.12.0 commit 94c21c2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.15.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
